 able to run Doom 3.  I've been told that it will run with my GeForce 2, but only with every single detail thing turned off, running in the lowest resolution possible.  They said that it's not one of those high paced games that you need 75fps to be good at.  It's more like Resident Evil where you occasionally encounter monsters that scare the crap out of you.  Of course, the monsters aren't going to hobble along and try to eat you, they'll jump at you and try to bite your head off.<br>
<br>
It's not due out until next year, so I'm sure the standards will change by then.  Your computer should be able to handle it, but if the game is a year away, you'll probably want to do some sort of upgrade before it, no? <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
